{"id":88088,"title":"Exudate: friend or foe?","abstract":"Wound exudate is an essential component in the normal process of wound healing. However, excess exudate has always been a major challenge for clinicians and a source of embarrassment and discomfort for the patient. The challenge for healthcare staff is to provide a wound healing environment that offers the optimal amount of exudate to promote healing. This article provides the reader with an understanding of the benefits and problems associated with exudate. ","date":"2014-06-10","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24912831","annotations":[{"name":"Health care","weight":0.472268,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care"},{"name":"Pain","weight":0.368345,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain"},{"name":"Natural environment","weight":0.180104,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_environment"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Clinic","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinic"},{"name":"Wound healing","weight":0.0334927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wound_healing"},{"name":"Exudate","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exudate"},{"name":"Wound","weight":0.0177912,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wound"},{"name":"Surface normal","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surface_normal"},{"name":"Academic major","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_major"},{"name":"Healing","weight":0.0159005,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Healing"},{"name":"Mathematical optimization","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_optimization"},{"name":"Embarrassment","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedi